\begin_layout Standard
In this section we examine features found in other MASs to see how they
 contrast with my system.
 The focus in the applied literature is on traffic and road network simulations.
 We review two papers that describe centralized versus distributed simulation
 systems
\begin_inset LatexCommand cite
key "france2003mso,10.1109/HICSS.2001.926331"

\end_inset

.
 One of them includes an implemented and installed system, while the other
 is evaluted using a mathematical formula describing variable levels of
 traffic congestion.
 Even excluding the fact that one is applied and the other more theoretical,
 their approaches are different enough to make a useful comparison.
 Then we look at coordination and cooperation among agents as opposed to
 competitive MASs
\begin_inset LatexCommand cite
key "wu2003umf"

\end_inset

.
 This paper uses the Belief-Desire-Intention (BDI) agent model to formulate
 a response to received inputs.
 Finally, we look at a recent review of MASs used for transport logistics
\begin_inset LatexCommand cite
key "davidsson2005aab"

\end_inset

, and identify where my software would be classified according to this scheme.
\end_layout

