 This is three-stage process.
 In stage 1 the local control agents repeatedly exchange utility information
 to find sets of compatible alternative signal plans.
 Stage 2 starts when one of the agents detects the completion of stage 1.
 This agent computes approximate probilities that each of the chosen sets
 of local signal plans would be enacted.
 In stage 3 a set of local signal plans are selected and the results are
 shared with all agents.
 This concludes the work of the autonomous agents in TRYSA
\begin_inset Formula $_{\text{2}}$
\end_inset

.
 At this stage in both systems the selected control plans are ready for
 review by the traffic engineer.
